name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: The identifier(s) of this adverse event that are assigned by business processes and/or used to refer to it when a direct URL reference to the resource itsefl is not appropriate.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The identifier(s) of this adverse event that are assigned by business processes and/or used to refer to it when a direct URL reference to the resource itsefl is not appropriate.

name: $category
desc: Returns: The type of event which is important to characterize what occurred and caused harm to the subject, or had the potential to cause harm to the subject.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The type of event which is important to characterize what occurred and caused harm to the subject, or had the potential to cause harm to the subject.

name: $::type
desc: Returns: This element defines the specific type of event that occurred or that was prevented from occurring.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: This element defines the specific type of event that occurred or that was prevented from occurring.

name: $subject
desc: Returns: This subject or group impacted by the event.  With a prospective adverse event, there will be no subject as the adverse event was prevented.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: This subject or group impacted by the event.  With a prospective adverse event, there will be no subject as the adverse event was prevented.

name: $date
desc: Returns: The date (and perhaps time) when the adverse event occurred.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The date (and perhaps time) when the adverse event occurred.

name: $reaction
desc: Returns: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

name: $addreaction
desc: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Includes information about the reaction that occurred as a result of exposure to a substance (for example, a drug or a chemical).

name: $location
desc: Returns: The information about where the adverse event occurred.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The information about where the adverse event occurred.

name: $seriousness
desc: Returns: Describes the seriousness or severity of the adverse event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Describes the seriousness or severity of the adverse event.

name: $outcome
desc: Returns: Describes the type of outcome from the adverse event.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Describes the type of outcome from the adverse event.

name: $recorder
desc: Returns: Information on who recorded the adverse event.  May be the patient or a practitioner.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Information on who recorded the adverse event.  May be the patient or a practitioner.

name: $eventParticipant
desc: Returns: Parties that may or should contribute or have contributed information to the Act. Such information includes information leading to the decision to perform the Act and how to perform the Act (e.g. consultant), information that the Act itself seeks to reveal (e.g. informant of clinical history), or information about what Act was performed (e.g. informant witness).

name: $description
desc: Returns: Describes the adverse event in text.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Describes the adverse event in text.

name: $suspectEntity
desc: Returns: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

name: $addsuspectEntity
desc: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Describes the entity that is suspected to have caused the adverse event.

desc: Returns: AdverseEvent.subjectMedicalHistory.

desc: AdverseEvent.subjectMedicalHistory.
